<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android">
  <!--
    Permissions are declared in the host app's app.json (see § Phase 1d
    in mobile/docs/gps-tracking-architecture.md). This manifest
    intentionally empty so the module adds no permissions on its own —
    the app author remains in control.

    The BroadcastReceiver for ActivityTransition events is registered
    dynamically from OtoqaMotionModule (lifecycle-bound to the JS
    registerTransitions call) rather than statically here. Rationale:
    a static receiver would survive app death and would need to route
    the event through a HeadlessJS task to restart the FGS. That
    dead-app wake path is a planned follow-up (see PR description); at
    Phase 1d scope AR fires only while the JS runtime is alive, and
    the FCM wake path (PR 1b) covers the dead-app case.
  -->
</manifest>
